Creating a real estate website involves several steps, from defining the structure to implementing features for showcasing properties, contact forms, and SEO. Below is a basic framework for your website, using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.


---

Website Code: Real Estate Hub

1. HTML (index.html)

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Dubai Property Hub</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Dubai Property Hub</h1>
            <nav>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#properties">Properties</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#about">About Us</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
                </ul>
            </nav>
        </div>
    </header>

    <section id="home">
        <div class="hero">
            <h2>Find Your Dream Property in Dubai</h2>
            <p>Luxury Villas, Apartments, and Offices.</p>
            <a href="#properties" class="btn">Explore Now</a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="properties">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Featured Properties</h2>
            <div class="property-list">
                <div class="property">
                    <img src="images/villa.jpg" alt="Luxury Villa">
                    <h3>Luxury Villa</h3>
                    <p>Price: 10,000,000 AED</p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn">View Details</a>
                </div>
                <div class="property">
                    <img src="images/apartment.jpg" alt="Modern Apartment">
                    <h3>Modern Apartment</h3>
                    <p>Price: 3,000,000 AED</p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn">View Details</a>
                </div>
                <div class="property">
                    <img src="images/office.jpg" alt="Office Space">
                    <h3>Office Space</h3>
                    <p>Price: 7,000,000 AED</p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn">View Details</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="about">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>About Us</h2>
            <p>We specialize in connecting clients with the finest properties in Dubai. Whether you're looking for a luxury villa, a modern apartment, or a professional office space, we provide top-notch services to help you find your dream property.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contact">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Contact Us</h2>
            <form id="contact-form">
                <input type="text" name="name" placeholder="Your Name" required>
                <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="Your Email" required>
                <textarea name="message" placeholder="Your Message" required></textarea>
                <button type="submit" class="btn">Send Message</button>
            </form>
        </div>
    </section>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 Dubai Property Hub. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>


---

2. CSS (styles.css)

body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    color: #333;
}

header {
    background-color: #008080;
    color: white;
    padding: 1rem 0;
}

header .container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0 2rem;
}

header nav ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
}

header nav ul li a {
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
}

.hero {
    background: url('images/dubai-skyline.jpg') no-repeat center center/cover;
    text-align: center;
    color: white;
    padding: 5rem 2rem;
}

.hero h2 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.btn {
    display: inline-block;
    background-color: #008080;
    color: white;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 5px;
}

.property-list {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    justify-content: space-between;
}

.property {
    border: 1px solid #ccc;
    padding: 1rem;
    text-align: center;
    flex: 1;
}

.property img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 200px;
    object-fit: cover;
}

footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1rem 0;
    background-color: #008080;
    color: white;
    margin-top: 2rem;
}


---

3. JavaScript (app.js)

document.getElementById("contact-form").addEventListener("submit", function (e) {
    e.preventDefault();
    alert("Thank you for your message! We will get back to you soon.");
});


---

4. Images

Add relevant property images (villa.jpg, apartment.jpg, office.jpg, dubai-skyline.jpg) to an images/ folder in the project directory.


---

Hosting the Website

1. Local Hosting:

Save the files in a folder.

Open the index.html file in a browser.



2. Online Hosting:

Use platforms like Netlify, GitHub Pages, or Vercel.

Upload your files to host your website for free.





---

Let me know if you want to customize it further or need help setting it up online!

